Mauritius Sugar Revenue to Rise 11% in 2011, l’Express Reports

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-08-17T07:28:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/mauritius-sugar-revenue-to-rise-11-in-2011-l-express-reports.html
Mauritius’s sugar revenue will
probably rise 11 percent per metric ton in 2011, l’Express
reported, citing Jean-Noel Humbert, chief executive officer of
the Mauritius Sugar Syndicate.  Revenue is expected to climb to 15,000 rupees ($536) a ton
compared with 13,535 rupees last year, the Port Louis-based
newspaper reported, as the country produces more refined and
specialty sugars.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
